29/09/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The new EU police mission to Macedonia that would succeed the military mission Concordia in December is to be called Proxima, according to Cristina Gallach, spokeswoman for EU security chief Javier Solana. She added that EU foreign ministers are to give formal approval to the mission Monday (29 September). It is to be composed of 200 members, who would assist the country in developing an efficient and professional police service and promote European police standards. (Dnevnik - 29/09/03; A1 TV - 27/09/03; MIA - 26/09/03)
